quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  28,71,"Fir`on said: \"How do you dare to believe in Him without my permission? This man must be your master, who taught you witchcraft. Well, I will cut off your hands and feet on alternate sides and crucify you on trunks of palm-trees; then you will know which one of us can give a more terrible and more lasting punishment"
  28,72,"The magicians replied: \"We can never prefer you, rather we prefer the miracle which we have witnessed and Him Who has created us. Therefore do whatever you will; you can only punish us in this worldly life"
  28,73,"As for us, we have believed in our Rabb so that He may forgive us our sins and the magic you have forced us to practice. Better is the ever lasting reward of Allah"
  28,74,Surely he who will come to his Rabb as a sinner shall be consigned to Hell - wherein he shall neither die nor live
  28,75,While he who will come to Him as a believer and has done good deeds shall have the highest ranks
  28,76,"Gardens of Eden, beneath which rivers flow, live therein forever; such is the reward of those who purify themselves from evil"
  28,77,"We sent Our revelation to Musa, saying: \"Set forth with my servants at night and strike a dry path for them through the sea without fear of being overtaken by Fir'on and without any fear while passing through the sea"